data = {"time":1643604014800,"blocks":[{"id":"hUa7YfP0SS","type":"Header","data":{"text":"Customizing Your Group","level":2}},{"id":"qLVO-F7BY0","type":"paragraph","data":{"text":"Once a group is created, you can truly make it YOUR group by clicking the \"Group Settings\" option from your group's interface. It is located in the top left of your screen, the icon is a cog."}},{"id":"zOrsloK4Ae","type":"image","data":{"url":"data:image/png;base64,","caption":"From here, you can choose to rename your group if you want, or upload a group icon.","withBorder":false,"withBackground":true,"stretched":false}},{"id":"xqXqXTkQpS","type":"paragraph","data":{"text":"You can also elect to make your group a private group from this screen, requiring approval from you before any more members join."}},{"id":"QRBHGsdwjP","type":"paragraph","data":{"text":"Here, you will also find the \"Delete Group\" option. After all, you brought it into this world, you have the power to take it out."}},{"id":"3KQIWkXVq7","type":"Header","data":{"text":"Muting a Group","level":2}},{"id":"SLySnDlYx8","type":"paragraph","data":{"text":"Whether it is your own group, or someone else's group that you joined, you have the option to mute notifications on your end from that specific group if things get a little too crowded."}},{"id":"p75KPuWH_5","type":"image","data":{"url":"data:image/png;base64,","caption":"The bell icon button labeled \"Mute Group\", when clicked, will silence all message notifications and icons from that group for you.","withBorder":false,"withBackground":true,"stretched":false}},{"id":"9D4lOFiGVW","type":"paragraph","data":{"text":"You can also mute a group by right clicking the group icon on the far left side of your screen, and selecting the drop down option \"Mute Group\".&nbsp;"}},{"id":"IBlGzc9R-R","type":"paragraph","data":{"text":"If you wish to unmute a group, simply relocate and click either one of the \"Mute Group\" buttons described above, which will now be labeled \"Unmute Group\"."}}],"version":"2.22.2","title":"Customize Group Settings and Appearances"}; runStart();